The battle for Libya's capital is taking a toll on people's lives as the holy month of Ramadan begins. Many shops are closed and businesses are struggling, as renegade military commander Khalifa Haftar's campaign to capture Tripoli shows no sign of stopping.  Libyan journalists protest against abduction of colleagues Libyan journalists protest in Tripoli against the abduction of Mohammed Al-Qurij and Mohammed Al-Shebani, who work for Libya's Al-Ahrar TV and have been kidnapped by an armed group said to be loyal to Khalifa Haftar.